14/07/2005
ANKARA, Turkey -- The foreign ministry said on Wednesday (13 July) that it has asked the Iraqi government to extradite two men suspected of preparing the bombings that rocked Istanbul in 2003.
Burhan Kus and Sadettin Akdas are Turkish nationals reportedly being held in an Iraqi prison.
Both are believed to have played a leading part in establishing an al-Qaeda cell in Turkey.
(NTV, Reuters, Guardian - 13/07/05)
